{{Top|leg}}
'''Imperial Machines''' was a weapons company that manufactured the [[I.M. mine]].

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|I.M. stands for "Imperial Machines," an outside contractor of Imperial weapons. I think Moff Rebus did some work for them but he hated their political infighting, and he wanted a more creative environment.|[[Justin Chin]]|<ref name="DF FAQ>{{WebCite|url=https://www.geocities.com/darkforces_faq/dftext2.html#DF51|text=Dark Forces FAQ|archivedate=20010422001343|nolive=1}}</ref>}}
Imperial Machines was named in a [[1996]] press release for the [[LucasArts]] video game ''[[Star Wars: Jedi Knight: Dark Forces II]]'', although not mentioned in the actual game. [[Justin Chin]], the writer and lead artist for ''Dark Forces'', has stated [[Moff/Legends|Moff]] [[Rebus (Galactic Empire)|Rebus]] worked for Imperial Machines, however, this has not been confirmed in any [[canon]] source.<ref name="DF FAQ />

